# Axodus Global Decisions

## Decision — Governance Has Constitutional And Local Nuclei

Axodus Governance has two distinct governance nuclei:

1. Constitutional Governance, powered by `$Neurons`.
2. Local Governance, controlled by each federated startup, DAO, company, product, or community.

Constitutional Governance defines federal standards, chain and plugin capabilities, constitutional conditions, ecosystem guardrails, treasury constraints, and ecosystem-wide legitimacy.

Local Governance may use `$Neurons`, local tokens, auto-generated platform tokens, multisigs, gauges, reputation systems, NFT governance, or plugin-defined models.

Local autonomy is allowed, but every local governance model must remain constitutionally compatible.

Opaque automatic exclusion language is not part of the Axodus governance model.

Governance restrictions must be represented as Constitutional Guardrails with transparent reason codes.

## Decision — Constitutional Layer Is Registry-Observable State

The Governance backend registry must expose a normalized Constitutional Governance layer for every chain.

This layer models:

* constitutional capabilities
* constitutional conditions
* authority model
* federation model
* execution model

Frontend surfaces may render this state, but they must not infer constitutional validity, sanctions, execution authority, treasury permissions, or federation membership.

The source of truth remains the registry, contracts, indexers, guardrails, and backend execution layers.

Harmony remains a legacy voting/spoke adapter and must not be represented as an Axodus constitutional execution chain.
